<div class="question-card" id="card-108" data-qid="108" data-type="single">
  <div class="card-header">
    <span class="q-number">Q 109</span>
    <span class="q-tag single">Single Choice</span>
  </div>
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="question-text">
      What characteristic describes an IPS?
    </p>
    <div class="options" id="opts-108">
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="0">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">A</span>
        <span class="opt-text">software that identifies fast-spreading threats</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">software on a router that filters traffic based on IP addresses or applications</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">a network device that filters access and traffic coming into a network</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">a tunneling protocol that provides remote users with secure access into the network of an organization</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-108" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-108">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-108"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        An IPS (Intrusion Prevention System) is characterized as software that identifies fast-spreading threats. It monitors network traffic for malicious activity and can take action to block or prevent threats in real-time, providing an additional layer of security beyond traditional firewalls.
      </div>
    </div>
